│ An analysis of the bug report indicates a crash in the LLVM loop vectorizer due to a type  │
│ mismatch during VPlan execution. The root cause is an incorrect type inference for `store` │
│ instructions within `VPTypeAnalysis`. The current implementation returns `void` for a      │
│ store's `VPReplicateRecipe`, but the vectorization process requires the type of the *value │
│ being stored*. This is especially problematic when type-widening optimizations are         │
│ performed, as in the provided reproducer, where an `i16` store is widened to an `i32`      │
│ store.                                                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to modify `VPTypeAnalysis::inferScalarTypeForRecipe` to correctly handle        │
│ `StoreInst`. Instead of returning `void`, it should recursively infer the type of the      │
│ value operand of the store. This ensures that the type analysis accounts for any           │
│ transformations applied to the value within the VPlan, resolving the type mismatch and     │
│ preventing the crash.                                                                      │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will now apply this fix.                                                                 │
